==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Upher
<hw>Up"her</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A
fir pole of from four to seven inches diameter, and twenty to forty feet
long, sometimes roughly hewn, used for scaffoldings, and sometimes for
slight and common roofs, for which use it is split.</def> <altsp>[Spelt
also <asp>ufer</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uphill</ent>⟦br⟧
